## Detection
| Source | Event ID | Indicator |
|---|---|---|
| Windows Security Log | 4662 | Replication rights used on domain object |
| Wazuh Rule 100031 | level 15 | DCSync detected — T1078.002 |
| Wazuh firedtimes | 53 | Repeated replication attempts |

## Active Response
```xml
<active-response>
  <command>firewall-drop</command>
  <location>local</location>
  <rules_id>100031</rules_id>
  <timeout>600</timeout>
</active-response>
```

### Known Limitation
firewall-drop on Wazuh Manager running inside Docker requires 
NET_ADMIN capability. Added to docker-compose.yml:
```yaml
cap_add:
  - NET_ADMIN
  - NET_RAW
```
In production, deploy a custom PowerShell active-response 
script directly on DC01 for immediate account isolation.

## Remediation
| Action | Priority |
|---|---|
| Remove WriteDACL from service accounts | CRITICAL |
| Monitor Event ID 4662 with replication GUIDs | CRITICAL |
| Implement tiered admin model | HIGH |
| Enable Protected Users Security Group | HIGH |
| Regular ACL audits via BloodHound | HIGH |
| Rotate krbtgt password immediately after detection | CRITICAL |
